<h4>Potato development and disease risk</h4>

<p>P-Days are the unit of thermal time used in a number of University of Wisconsin-Extension potato management products. Accumulation of potato p-days is particularly useful in assessing the risk of early blight development. To learn more, visit the <%= link_to "Vegetable Pathology Lab website", "https://vegpath.plantpath.wisc.edu" %> or the <%= link_to "Integrated Pest and Crop Management website", "http://ipcm.wisc.edu/" %>. To view potato disease risk models, visit the <%= link_to "Vegetable Disease and Insect Forecasting Network website", vdifn_path %>.</p>

<h4>Potato Pests</h4>

<p>For information on potato pests such as the Colorado Potato Beetle, see our <%= link_to "degree-day calculator", action: :degree_days %> page or visit the <%= link_to "UW Vegetable Entomology website", vegento_url %>. To view potato insect development models, visit the <%= link_to "Vegetable Disease and Insect Forecasting Network website", vdifn_path %></p>

